        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> Wednesday&#44; <date><hi rend="underline"
                        >Oct.&#8211;Jan.</hi>&#63;&#44; 1847</date>./</p>
            <p>God who will bring joy to Zion&#44; etc. May he<lb/> bring joy to the soul of my
                friend&#44; etc.&#44; etc.</p>
            <p>Sir&#58;</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">At first glance your letter of last week&#44; I did not understand<lb/> thing about
                its contents&#44; since it was written in English&#44; and&#44; up to the
                    pres<add>&#63;</add><lb/> I cannot understand your wishes&#44; for the letters
                are run&#8211;together<lb/> require more knowledge than I possess
                &#40;&#63;&#41;&#44; Therefore&#44; I beg your pardon a<add>nd</add><lb/> ask you
                from now on to write in German or in Hebrew. I still have in <add>my</add><lb/>
                possession the sum of &#36;7.50. I have not as yet received a penny&#39;s
                    wor<add>th</add><lb/> from the prayer books or the pentateuchs. For any number
                that came to<lb/>
                <lb/> I had to tell them that I should send the books on the next day&#44;<lb/>
                however&#44; the prayer books are in my possession&#44; for I received
                    the<add>m</add><lb/> last week through Adams and Company. I shall make every
                    eff<add>ort</add><lb/> to sell what I can. If you want the above mentioned
                sum&#44; p<add>&#63;</add><lb/> remind me&#44; and I shall send it to you without
                any delay.<lb/> With regard to the printing of my book&#44; I shall print two
                page<lb/> next week and <persName>Mr. Jackson</persName> here will print them. If I
                succeed<lb/> finding the printing expenses through subscribers&#44; I shall come
                to<lb/> city to make an agreement with <persName>Mr. Johnson</persName> and will
                give him two<lb/> as references&#44; or the printer himself will buy them. With all
                this&#44;<lb/> heart says to you&#44; many thanks for the thought which is
                    equival<add>ent</add><lb/> to an action.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">May the king of heaven increase you and give you length of da<add>ys</add><lb/> to
                occupy yourself in communal needs in honesty&#44; and <del>mak</del> m<add>&#63;</add><lb/> you
                continue to9 serve God&#39;s name&#44; and may you behold
                the<lb/> coming of the Announcer and the Redeemer and to see the
                gat<add>&#63;</add><lb/> of the scattered sheep and the rebuilding of the sacred
                mount<lb/> in <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName> and its renewal in the near
                future&#44; Amen&#433;</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">From me&#44; the <add>&#63;</add>&#44; who seeks your peace and your
                    goo<add>&#63;</add><lb/> all your days.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><persName role="author">Simon Cohen Noot</persName><lb/> &#35;6 James Street.</p>

